data.title: sepora • west-sydney creative
data.content:
I spent half the weekend doing family things, and the other half doing my own thing (but feeling guilty about not spending the whole weekend with my family... working on that guilt thing I swear 🤦🏾‍♀️).⁣⁣
⁣⁣
My parents are still learning the art of compromise, and I’m working very hard to make my living situation work. Domestic violence is real. PTSD is real. Depression and anxiety are real. I’m working through it all, or it will consume me otherwise.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s a photograph of one of my weekend highlights, and something that I’d like to remember when things get tough. My mum knocked on my door to show me her first homegrown pumpkin harvest. A photo shoot (of course) ensued. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Excellent green thumbs, this teine mai Lepa 💚⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#GreenThumb #Homegrown #MentalHealth #canon550d
